a3643 20
With
.Nm lex ,
the following:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
NAME    [A-Z][A-Z0-9]*
%%
foo{NAME}?      printf("Found it\en");
%%
.Ed
.Pp
will not match the string
.Qq foo
because when the macro is expanded the rule is equivalent to
.Qq foo[A-Z][A-Z0-9]*?
and the precedence is such that the
.Sq ?\&
is associated with
.Qq [A-Z0-9]* .
With
.Nm ,
d3645 2
a3646 5
.Qq foo([A-Z][A-Z0-9]*)?
and so the string
.Qq foo
will match.
